Aldgate
[trigger none]
[vignette intro/city_gates]

The caravan has crawled across weeks of bitter miles, wheels grinding in ruts of dust and mud. You have endured countless cold nights, thin meals, and the dry stink of pack beasts and old leather.

At long last, you stand outside Aldgate, among weathered crates and trade cloth and dusty barrels. The caravan master is arguing with a growing cluster of imperial functionaries. The man looks to you for help, but you don't meet his gaze. You'll have trouble enough on your own in the city; this man can sort his own affairs.

The delay stretches on, and the caravan idles in the road like a beast made to kneel. Nothing moves but the wind worrying the banners above the gate and the restless shifting of pack mules.

There is an unfamiliar weight on you hand.

